[[div class="addendum"]]

[[div style="border-bottom: 2px solid #275495;"]]
[[/div]]

= **[BEGIN LOG]**

[[div style="border-bottom: 2px solid #275495;"]]
[[/div]]

//There is brief silence, then the sound of Crenshaw clearing his throat.//

**Crenshaw:** What the hell is it that you think you're doing?

//Al Fine chuckles.//

**D.C. al Fine:** Ah, Mr. President. I've been expecting you. I'm glad you didn't disappoint.

**Crenshaw:** Yeah, very fucking funny. //<Pause>// Listen, because I'll only say this once: get your dirty mage hands out of my office. This is //my// country, you hear that? The enactment of the Pizzicato would be equivalent to a declaration of war--

//Al Fine's smile drops. Her tone is ice-cold.//

**D.C. al Fine:** A war you would certainly lose, yes. And did I hear that right? Do you suddenly not want our support? I thought you liked the idea of dumping your dirty work on us.

**Crenshaw:** Woman, listen--

**D.C. al Fine:** No, you listen, //boy//. You came to my doorstep begging for help the second your little pet project got out of control. You thought we were still the weak Coalition you saw after Silesia, slowly fading away in a world where [[[i-did-not-fade|the occult is the norm]]]. You actually believed we would deal with you and PENTAGRAM's little fuck up in exchange for Uncle Sam's support? Don't make me laugh. Here's a hard pill for you to swallow: you are not the one pulling the strings here, Crenshaw.

**D.C. al Fine:** Whether you like it or not, you invited us in. You're lucky we haven't barged in ourselves the moment we sniffed trouble. Truth be told we should have done that, the second we saw the Carter money in your account. But now that we're here, you'll have to deal with us like a man.

**Crenshaw:** You were called in to deal with an emergency. You were called in to //do your job//, not to occupy a sovereign nation, let alone execute Pizzicato. This is outside our agreement. Who do you think you are?

**D.C. al Fine:** From the moment I heard your little whining over the phone four months ago, I knew this was going to be a mess, and once again, you haven't failed to disappoint. The Pizzicato vote is a show of strength, you dimwit, one that worked perfectly, looking at your reaction.

**D.C. al Fine:** America has thought for far too long that it can make fools out of us, just like you did back in '51. But here's the thing -- you are not old Truman, and neither Stan Bowe nor the Foundation are here to come and save your ass. Welcome to the world of //realpolitik//, boy.

**Crenshaw:** How dare you talk to me like that? I should have let Bowe take you out the second he told me a faggot like you--

**D.C. al Fine:** Call me that again, and I swear to you upon my honor that I will actually declare Pizzicato and raze your country to the ground. You think you're still in control, Dan? Hoping my Council will outvote me, hoping there's still a chance you'll escape from this without handing your control over?

**D.C. al Fine:** Well, let me tell you something: the Council answers to //me//, not vice versa. Hold your hope all you want, but I swear to all that is holy that if you ever dare to question my authority again, I will personally come down to your little House in Washington.

//There is a pause.//

**D.C. al Fine:** So. Have I made myself clear?

//Another pause.//

**Crenshaw:** You have no idea who you're dealing with.

**D.C. al Fine:** And neither do you.

[[div style="border-bottom: 2px solid #275495;"]]
[[/div]]

= **[END LOG]**

